¥section*{7. Investment growth}

Given
¥[
f(t)=a¥cdot 2^{¥frac{2t}{11}}.
¥]

The initial investment is
¥[
f(0)=a.
¥]

An increase by $700¥%$ means the new amount is
¥[
100¥%+700¥%=800¥%
¥]
of the original, so the new amount is
¥[
8a.
