¥section*{23. Means of two data sets}

Let the sum of the four numbers in data set A be $S$. Then its mean is
¥[
¥frac{S}{4}.
¥]

Data set B adds one more number $x$, so its mean is
¥[
¥frac{S+x}{5}.
¥]

The difference is
¥[
¥frac{S}{4}-¥frac{S+x}{5}
=¥frac{5S-4S-4x}{20}
=¥frac{S-4x}{20}.
¥]

To maximize this difference, make the mean of A as large as possible and the added number as small as possible.

Largest possible mean of A:
¥[
20
¥]
(by choosing all four numbers as $20$).

Smallest possible added number:
¥[
10.
¥]

So the largest possible difference is
¥[
20-¥frac{20+20+20+20+10}{5}
=20-¥frac{90}{5}
=20-18=2.
¥]

¥[
¥boxed{2}
¥]

¥section*{24. Frequency table}

