So I is true.

¥textbf{II.} The standard deviation of set B equals that of set A.

Multiplying every value by $2$ multiplies the standard deviation by $2$, not keeps it the same. So II is false.

¥textbf{III.} The range of set B is double the range of set A.

Range of A:
¥[
5-1=4.
¥]
Range of B:
¥[
10-2=8.
¥]
Yes, it doubles. III is true.

So I and III only.

