¥section*{25. Margin of error}

The estimate is
¥[
60¥%¥pm 5¥%.
¥]
So a plausible interval for the proportion of ¥textbf{11th graders} in at least one AP class is
¥[
55¥%¥text{ to }65¥%.
¥]

¥textbf{I.} ``It is not possible for just $40¥%$ of the 11th graders ...''

This is too strong. A sample estimate does not prove something is impossible. So I is not an appropriate conclusion.

¥textbf{II.} ``It is plausible that the proportion of ¥emph{all students at the school} ...''

The sample was from ¥textbf{11th graders only}, so we cannot generalize to all students at the school. So II is not appropriate.

¥textbf{III.} ``If the sample size is increased, the margin of error will drop below $5¥%$.''

A larger sample size decreases the margin of error, so this is appropriate.

Therefore only III is correct.

